 memorable itinerary, thanks to his extensive knowledge of the Balearics. Considered an active and friendly person, his main motivation is to create a good atmosphere on the yacht and ensuring that everyone is enjoying the charter. The most important for him is to have happy guests on board. He loves discovering new places and sharing the ones he knows, but also doing water sports, such as kitesurf, paddle and diving."},{"name":"Nelia Popovych","role":"Captain","bio":"Ukrainian\n\nCombining her two passions, sailing and cooking, Nelia is a perfect fit as a yacht Chef onboard CALMA. Mastering Mediterranean, Asian and other cuisines from the whole world, she offers versatile menus. Nelia is creative with the presentation and flexible, subject to guests’ requirements, always having mind any allergies, intolerance, or special diets they may have. It is always helpful for her to get as much information as possible from the guests so she can fully adapt to their expectations and bring them the best culinary experience on board. She likes working with a team and is always trying to make everyone happy during charters."},{"name":"Carlos Caruzzo","role":"Captain","bio":"Argentinian\n\nBorn in Argentina and Spanish nationality. Carlos speaks Spanish and basic English. He has lived since he was 20 years old in Spain, Province of Alicante on the Costa Blanca, lover of the sea and nautical sports, he has been working in the nautical industry for 16 and a half years.\n\n"}],"pricing":{"weekPricingFrom":{"currency":"EUR","price":4050000,"displayCurrency":"EUR","displayPrice":4050000,"unit":"WEEK"},"weekPricingTo":{"currency":"EUR","price":4650000,"displayCurrency":"EUR","displayPrice":4650000,"unit":"WEEK"},"pricingInfo":[{"name":"Low Season (May and October)","effectiveDates":[{"from":"2026-05-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2026-05-31T23:59:59.999Z"},{"from":"2027-05-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2027-05-31T23:59:59.999Z"},{"from":"2028-05-01T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2028-05-31T23:59:59.999Z"},{"